# ============================================================
# SOCIAL CORE ARCHITECTURE
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: architecture
domain: social
scope: social.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

purpose:
Defines the canonical architectural role of social in CivilizationOS.

design_intent:
This domain exists as an explicit governed structure
rather than an informal bucket.

required_behavior:
- domain identity must be explicit
- role structure must be explicit
- activity scope must be explicit
- authority/boundary meaning must be explicit
- validation must be explicit
- failure conditions must be reviewable

canonical_rules:
- projections must not overwrite truth
- ambiguity fails closed
- state transitions must remain reviewable

state_model:
The domain distinguishes
registered state,
active state,
restricted state,
historical state,
and closed state.

transition_rules:
Transitions must preserve identity,
boundary,
activity meaning,
and reviewability.

review_checklist:
- identity is explicit
- roles are explicit
- activity scope is explicit
- boundaries are explicit
- transition rules are explicit
